IIS_ASPNET_EXECPTIONS_THROWN_PER_SECOND.description: Number of exceptions per second that the application is throwing.

IIS_ASPNET_REQUESTS_PER_SECOND.description: Shows the throughput o the ASP.NET application on the server.

IIS_ASPNET_REQUESTS_QUEUED.description: The number of request that are in the queue to be processed.

IIS_ASPNET_REQUEST_WAIT_TIME.description: Shows the amount of time that the last request was held in the queue.

IIS_ASPNET_RESTARTS.description: Indicates the number of restarts of the application in the server's uptime.

IIS_ASPNET_TOTAL_COMMITTED_BYTES.description: Amount of virtual memory reserved for the application on the paging file.

IIS_GENERAL_CPU_QUEUE_LENGTH.description: The processor queue is being filled up with threads when the server's processor are busy servicing other threads at the moment.

IIS_GENERAL_CPU_USAGE.description: Average percentage of processor time occupied

IIS_GENERAL_DISK_TIME.description: Refers to the percentage of time the disk was occupied.

IIS_GENERAL_MEMORY_FREE.description: Refers to the amount of physical memory on the system that can be used by new processes.

IIS_GENERAL_MEMORY_PAGE_PER_SECOND.description: Refers to the amount of read and write request from memory to disk.

IIS_GENERAL_NETWORK_BYTES_PER_SECOND.description: Refers to the total amount of bytes over the network.

IIS_SERVICE_CURRENT_CONNECTIONS.description: Number of active connections with the Web Service.

IIS_SERVICE_GET_REQUESTS_PER_SECOND.description: Amount of GET requests processed in a second.

IIS_SERVICE_POST_REQUESTS_PER_SECOND.description: Amount of POST requests processed in a second.
